Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.31,0:00:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut cases are even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.65,0:00:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.52,0:00:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case is\Nabout the acting spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.15,0:00:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great actor\Nversus great detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.05,0:00:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.77,0:00:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.79,0:00:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.04,0:01:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijikata Kozaburo-{\i1}san{\i0}, the historical\Ndrama actor, hired the old guy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.22,0:02:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and showed us to his home on the 5th floor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of an apartment building.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:03.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijikata
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.56,0:02:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While we were on the veranda,\Ntaking in the view,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.89,0:02:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the dead body of Isami, Kozaburo's\Nwife, collapsed onto the veranda
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.44,0:02:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of Okita Hajime,\Nwho lived next door!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.32,0:02:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okita was home,\Nbut denies killing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.24,0:02:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, the police and the\Nold guy are convinced he did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.20,0:02:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, having seen a smile on\NHijikata's face instead of sadness,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.87,0:02:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I started to doubt it was Okita...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.25,0:02:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and finally found the proof to flip\Nthe case completely upside-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.42,0:02:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Historical Drama\NActor Murder Case (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are a lot more\Nhere than I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.15,0:02:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan! Go back to where Ran is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.78,0:02:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.07,0:03:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?\NWhere are you, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird. Where could he be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.62,0:03:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, have you seen Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he's in my apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.79,0:03:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.64,0:03:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.23,0:03:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.98,0:03:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He's not here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.82,0:03:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he wouldn't be.\NHis shoes weren't at the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured out the trick.\NBut there's still no proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.87,0:03:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could probably corner Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.42,0:03:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by showing everyone\Nthis strange sight...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.17,0:03:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'd really prefer to\Nhave some definitive proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.\NAre you really not here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.05,0:04:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. If only we had touched\Nmuch more obvious stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.47,0:04:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Wait. As I recall...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.98,0:04:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.32,0:04:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, given the old guy's personality,\Nit should be around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No question about it!\NHijikata-{\i1}san {\i0}is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used this trick to deceive us\Nand lead us to this deceptive place!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.88,0:04:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mori! Is it true there\Nwas a murder in this building?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! You can tell us, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.89,0:04:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that the deceased is\NNagakura Isami, the former actress,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that you've been to\Nthe murder scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.94,0:04:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. I'd like to have a smoke first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do things look\Nin there, Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.24,0:05:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san {\i0}has the press' undivided\Nattention by the front entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.74,0:05:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reporters at the back entrance\Nhave started to come to the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.62,0:05:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Just as we planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.08,0:05:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While Mori-{\i1}kun\N{\i0}has them distracted,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll bring the suspect, Okita-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nand the witness, Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.55,0:05:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,down from the 5th floor, and head\Nto the station out the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.26,0:05:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Mr. Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.02,0:05:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.39,0:05:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-{\i1}ojisan {\i0}said he\Nhas a favor to ask you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.86,0:05:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.23,0:05:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.53,0:05:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us about the incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.24,0:05:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems fishy if you ask me!\NI bet you don't know anything at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.58,0:05:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:06:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you just\None hint! Now come close!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.79,0:06:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okita Hajime is the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.38,0:06:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The actor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.92,0:06:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is still a secret!\NDon't let the inspector hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.22,0:06:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're certain, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.85,0:06:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw Isami-{\i1}san {\i0}collapse\Nonto the veranda next door
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.90,0:06:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from her husband's own veranda?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.61,0:06:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that veranda belongs to\NOkita Hajime, who lives on the 5th floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when the\Npolice rushed in afterward,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.91,0:06:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,both the body\Nand Okita were there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.08,0:06:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd mean Okita Hajime\Nwas clearly the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.75,0:06:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, pretty much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Big scoop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This'll be tonight's top news!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.51,0:06:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me! Get a camera and\Nnewscaster here on the double!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.22,0:06:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a breaking story!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.64,0:06:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.81,0:06:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.14,0:07:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, that wasn't me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.28,0:07:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.69,0:07:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have more information?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now to use this\Nvoice-changer to talk for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.79,0:07:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it would seem clear\Nthat Okita-{\i1}san {\i0}killed her,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.79,0:07:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that isn't the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.58,0:07:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?!\NPlease explain, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.63,0:07:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Hurry out the back door\Nwhile Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s distracting them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.22,0:07:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying someone\Nelse killed her, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.27,0:07:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The killer used a trick to\Nfool my eyes into seeing it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.57,0:07:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right? The real killer,\Nwho's trying to sneak out the back...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.70,0:07:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Hijikata Kozaburo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:07:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.04,0:08:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Hijikata Kozaburo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.04,0:08:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Okita Hajime!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.17,0:08:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, now! Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.38,0:08:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here, Inspector Megure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.84,0:08:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is what Detective Mori said true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do the police consider a suspect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.26,0:08:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.10,0:08:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori! Knock this off!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.27,0:08:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, how could it be Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.64,0:08:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was with you when\Nyou saw Isami-{\i1}san {\i0}fall over!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.28,0:08:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, the fishing line used to strangle her
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was found in Okita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s apartment!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.45,0:08:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was even in his 5th floor apartment,\Nwhere the body was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.83,0:08:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the murder took place!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could anyone else have\Ncarried the body into his room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.50,0:08:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the killer really is Okita Hajime?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.38,0:08:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was his motive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell us it had to do\Nwith his affair with Isami-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.01,0:09:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I'm not at liberty to--!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be questioning\Nhim soon about all of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.69,0:09:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, given these circumstances,\NHijikata-{\i1}san {\i0}couldn't have done it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.27,0:09:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Okita-{\i1}san {\i0}clearly seems to be the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming the veranda we\Nwitnessed Isami-{\i1}san {\i0}fall onto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.33,0:09:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was really on the 5th floor, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.41,0:09:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?! What do you mean, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.09,0:09:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming the veranda we\Nwitnessed Isami-{\i1}san {\i0}fall onto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.43,0:09:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was really on the 5th floor, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?! What do you mean, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose cell phone is that?! Turn it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's mine, Inspector. It seems\Nto have rung at the perfect time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.45,0:10:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What nonsense is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.41,0:10:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying your cell phone\Nwill help explain the incident?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.45,0:10:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Please take it from my pants pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.83,0:10:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of your men is taking a look
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.42,0:10:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the unusual\Nsight Hijikata-{\i1}san {\i0}created.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Takagi? Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.01,0:10:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you call Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s phone?\NWhere are you, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The living room in Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Nextra apartment on the 6th floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.82,0:10:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.36,0:10:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? It's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.74,0:10:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same. The TV, the sofa,\Nthe curtains, the table...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.41,0:10:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even their positions are the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.04,0:10:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all exactly identical to his\Nliving room directly below this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.42,0:10:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Exactly identical?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.55,0:10:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.67,0:11:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only difference\Nis that the 5th floor room
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has four cups filled\Nwith tea on the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.14,0:11:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the 6th floor table is bare...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the meaning of this, Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are your living rooms on the\N5th and 6th floors exactly alike?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.65,0:11:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was to fool me into thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.87,0:11:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Isami-{\i1}san {\i0}collapsed on the 5th\Nfloor veranda, rather than the 6th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.54,0:11:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.41,0:11:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.62,0:11:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After he took me to his\Nfake room on the 6th floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.17,0:11:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijikata-{\i1}san {\i0}had me wait in the living room
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.34,0:11:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while he strangled\NIsami-{\i1}san {\i0}in the 5th floor room
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.43,0:11:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and carried her to the 6th floor\Nroom directly above Okita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.39,0:11:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He set things up so she would\Nfall onto the veranda at the right time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.56,0:11:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then returned to the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.03,0:12:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pretending to have had\Na hard time preparing the tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.66,0:12:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He then invited me onto the veranda,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.53,0:12:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and, at just the right time, he used\Nhis cell phone's speed-dial button.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.92,0:12:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had the sound of the\Nphone next door attract our attention
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.50,0:12:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we would witness Isami-{\i1}san\N{\i0}falling onto the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.97,0:12:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did it in such a way
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.01,0:12:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it looked like it had been\NOkita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s veranda one floor below!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.52,0:12:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that can't be right. Her body\Nreally was in Okita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.48,0:12:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. Hear me out, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.78,0:12:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, Hijikata-{\i1}san {\i0}ran straight to the next-door apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:46.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Okita
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.36,0:12:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and shouted and pounded on\Nthe door, but without reply, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.91,0:12:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because it wasn't Okita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Napartment, but Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:13:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the rooms on the 6th floor\Nbelong to Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.92,0:13:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterward, while I went\Ndownstairs to get the spare key,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0} entered the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.01,0:13:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and used the\Nrope he had prepared
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.27,0:13:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to lower Isami-{\i1}san {\i0}to\NOkita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s veranda below.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.31,0:13:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With rope?! H-How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.77,0:13:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably wrapped\Nthe rope under her arms,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.94,0:13:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lifted her over, lowered her down,\Nswung her onto the veranda,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.82,0:13:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then pulled the rope free.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.16,0:13:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, her body has a scrape\Nmark from when he pulled the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the scrapes all over her body
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.38,0:13:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are from when she was\Nswung onto the veranda?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a dangerous and\Nunreliable method,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.68,0:13:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the veranda faces the river,\Nso the chance of being seen was slim,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:13:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,plus, even if he\Naccidentally dropped her,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.36,0:14:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he could explain it away by\Nsaying the killer threw her over
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.23,0:14:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the heat of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.74,0:14:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After lowering Isami-{\i1}san{\i0}'s body,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.45,0:14:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijikata-{\i1}san {\i0}put the 6th floor\Nroom number plate back to normal,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,hurried to Okita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s door\None floor below,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.58,0:14:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then nonchalantly waited\Nfor me to bring the spare key.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.97,0:14:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if he had been\Nwaiting there the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.97,0:14:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But could he really lower the body,\Nreplace the plate, and all that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while you were getting the key?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could easily buy that much\Ntime by stopping the elevator above.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.36,0:14:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijikata-{\i1}san {\i0}probably did many\Ntest runs to figure out the timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}! You took the elevator\Nwhen he first brought you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you realize\Nyou were on the 6th floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.96,0:15:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The floor number display\Nwould've made it obvious right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.26,0:15:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. From the moment\NI got on the elevator,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}'s spell\Nwas already at work on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.44,0:15:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, Inspector. Have a look\Nat the elevator's floor number display.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.52,0:15:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still a little bit left...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.86,0:15:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Signs of the trick he used to\Nlead me to his place of deception!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that black smudge?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.59,0:15:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's most likely black marker\Nink that he failed to wipe away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.97,0:16:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He marked out the\Nvertical line on the lower left
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.85,0:16:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make the 6 look like a 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.98,0:16:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have thought of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.73,0:16:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}!\NThen what about "2"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.36,0:16:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's as you say, then that'd\Nmake the number 2 look strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.70,0:16:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I was cleverly fooled there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.08,0:16:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He gave us his business\Ncard inside the elevator,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while his back covered the floor buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.04,0:16:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! That would\Ndirect your eyes to the cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.92,0:16:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and hide the floor buttons\Nand display from view...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.89,0:16:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably wiped the ink off\Nwhen he stopped the elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.60,0:16:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My only chance to see the strange\N"2" was when I went downstairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.44,0:16:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was in a hurry\Nand there was no time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.99,0:16:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so fast, detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.70,0:16:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been saying,\N"trick this, deception that,"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.37,0:17:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and claiming I'm some criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.04,0:17:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have proof that I killed Isami?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.75,0:17:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Proof that I took you to\Nthe 6th floor instead of the 5th?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.05,0:17:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how do you explain that\Nthe living rooms on both floors
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.38,0:17:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are exactly the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.89,0:17:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Is something wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.76,0:17:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I happen to like that furniture and layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.31,0:17:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you accuse, could we\Nsee this infallible proof of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, this is nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.53,0:17:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.65,0:17:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your confidence must mean\Nthat you wiped away our fingerprints
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.53,0:17:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from everything we might've\Ntouched in the 6th floor room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.20,0:17:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.71,0:17:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would surmise you wiped\Nthem away while I was downstairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.71,0:17:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when you hurriedly took away\Nthe teacups in the 6th floor room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.84,0:17:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurriedly took away?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.51,0:17:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.84,0:18:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that Detective Takagi was\Nable to enter the 6th floor room easily
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.14,0:18:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,means he made the grave blunder\Nof forgetting to lock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.81,0:18:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you! Show some proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.32,0:18:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. Please confirm\Nwith Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.49,0:18:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask if there's anything odd on the\Nfloor of the 6th floor living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.70,0:18:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The floor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Is there anything\Nunusual on the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.84,0:18:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Anything unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.26,0:18:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is something!\NA metallic, pointed thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A metallic, pointed thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, please flip over\Nthe cushions of the nearby sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something I quickly\Nhid should be there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.65,0:18:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with my fingerprints on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.20,0:19:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Inspector! A model gun!\NThere's a model gun under the cushion!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.74,0:19:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A model gun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.04,0:19:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.29,0:19:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}! You're certain your\Nfingerprints are on this model gun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.17,0:19:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I broke it while waiting\Nfor Hijikata-{\i1}san {\i0}in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have the courage to tell him,\Nso I hid it under the cushion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never did I imagine it would\Nbe the key to breaking the spell
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}'s trick like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.02,0:19:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume you realize, Hijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.49,0:19:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was with you in Okita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s room\Nthe entire time after the murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.91,0:19:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I was with Inspector Megure\Nwhen I came down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.21,0:19:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, unless I'd been\Nin that 6th floor room from the start...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I wouldn't have been\Nable to touch that model gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.72,0:20:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, the trick to\Nmaking Isami-{\i1}san {\i0}fall over
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.89,0:20:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was probably done by holding her\Nup with fishing line over a rail,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.69,0:20:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the line would break or\Ncome undone when the time came.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.61,0:20:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. Please inspect the\Nroom directly above Okita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.53,0:20:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Traces of his set-up might still be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.50,0:20:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not "might." It's definitely still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.54,0:20:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mechanism I used to\Nmake Isami's body fall on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.80,0:20:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you admit to killing her,\NHijikata-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.64,0:20:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was I, Hijikata Kozaburo,\Nwho murdered my wife Isami!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had to pay for getting\Ntogether with this lowlife,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.61,0:21:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I wanted the money\Nto rebuild my film studio!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.40,0:21:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The money from her insurance, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.40,0:21:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that, all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.53,0:21:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, when did you figure it out, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.62,0:21:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the sound of Okita-{\i1}san{\i0}'s phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.67,0:21:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was different from\Nwhat I heard on the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.04,0:21:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's odd. I'm certain I prepared\Na phone with the same sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.97,0:21:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to buy a new one yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.59,0:21:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I have no luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.93,0:21:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, the main cause of\Nyour downfall was probably that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.81,0:21:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you underestimated Mori-{\i1}kun\N{\i0}and had him witness your trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.90,0:21:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never underestimated him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.69,0:21:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.32,0:21:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had I been able to completely\Nfool the great Mori-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.20,0:21:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've made a great detective\Nin my first modern drama role.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.01,0:23:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.39,0:23:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the great detective\NMori Kogoro for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.77,0:23:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}! How does it feel to have\Ncaught a historical drama actor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.73,0:23:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.40,0:23:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I feel like\NToyama-no-Kin-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.74,0:23:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a real star!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.37,0:23:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This clown is such a pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.50,0:24:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.22,0:24:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's crazy, Dad! All the clocks\Nin the house are ringing!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.18,0:24:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! The entire house?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.10,0:24:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the VCR is running...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.18,0:24:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly is going to happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.02,0:24:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.57,0:24:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Case of the Mysterious\NBandit Mansion (Part 1)"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.06,0:24:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.29,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.46,0:24:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode features lots of clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.84,0:24:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I smell a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.54,0:24:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you late?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.48,0:24:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.89,0:24:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
